{"author":{"id":"458c2786e2fb21c7f2463be283bdb1d457c6c22ed9854985782318ab918e2e3f"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1454103914,"nonce":"b61K7Z7PQler+mpAtG1aQSOtc+8=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDE3Njk4MjQ3OQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/583#issuecomment-176982479"},"message":"This is implemented in the wrapper as a selection between p-value, q-value, and fold enrichment for peak detection. However, looking at the docs for MACS2, p-value and q-value appear to be mutually exclusive options as cutoffs for peak detection, while fold enrichment is implemented as a post-processing step only to filter out peaks.\n\nThus, I would propose that fold enrichment be moved to a separate parameter in the \"Advanced\" section and set to the default of 1.0. Also, it should be `--fe-cutoff FECUTOFF`.\n\nOn a related note, I don't see why `--call-summits` is only available when ``broad-peaks` is not selected.","files":null}]}